snippet.textDisplay:
Falun Dafa practitioners participated in Middletown’s Tree Lighting Ceremony & Parade again this year, bringing ancient Chinese culture to their local community as they demonstrated the five Falun Dafa exercises, performed the dragon dance, and played the waist drums.

The annual parade started after dark, at 6:30 p.m. on November 29, 2019. The procession began at Run 4 Downtown Park on North Street, proceeded to West Main Street, and concluded at Festival Square.
